cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.NE, cs.SI

The paper discusses a clustering approach for gene expression data using Fuzzy Soft sets and Rough sets. This falls under the domain of machine learning and data mining, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The use of clustering algorithms and comparative analysis with benchmark algorithms suggests that the paper is likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on gene expression data and cluster validity measures suggests that it could also belong to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of similarity relationships and efficient grouping of functionally related genes suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
